pi.github.com/users/nblumhardt/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2016-05-11T02:41:46Z","updated_at":"2016-05-11T02:41:46Z","body":"I know it is a bit hacky, but what about if we implemented a `TextWriter` (as supplied to `SelfLog.Out`) on top of `ILogger`?\n\n``` csharp\nvar internal = new LoggerConfiguration().WriteTo.Whatever().CreateLogger();\nSelfLog.Out = new LogWriter(internal);\n```\n\nThis could be cleaned up and encapsulated with:\n\n``` csharp\nvar internal = new LoggerConfiguration().WriteTo.Whatever().CreateLogger();\nSelfLog.Logger = internal; // Sets SelfLog.Out\n```\n\nHas the nice effect of emulating `Log.Logger`.\n\nBut, **serious** footgun territory if any part of the internal logger itself writes to `SelfLog` (this was the impetus for separating them and using a `TextWriter` originally). May be some tricky way to avoid this, but not an obvious/clean one I can see.....\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/serilog/serilog/issues/comments/218347542/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"nblumhardt","id":342712,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MjcxMg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/342712?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt","html_url":"https://github.com/nblumhardt","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumhardt/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nblumha